Process to add new leagues' channel data:

1. Create new league's tab in Upcoming Schedule document

https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1gGY9dr485hf4WrdGkx01kC6Gw7oTuKeYYh_UQD5qkt4/edit?gid=50932962#gid=50932962




2. Grab schedule and convert to CSV in Cursor:

Give me the following data in CSV format in these columns: Date, Time, Away Team, Home Team, Channel.  Add 1 hour to every time you see.  Put date in 9/13/2025 format. Add only the first channel for each game.  Give me the csv results in code block.






3. Data > Split text to columns




4. Format Date, Time, Plain Text



**SKIP THIS STEP IF NOT A NEW LEAGUE, IF JUST ADDING UPCOMING SCHEDULE FOR EXISTING LEAGUE**
5. Add league's team name mapping to Google Apps Script (google-sheets-team-converter.js):

Convert all team names for this league from output to input

Output is the league names from Flashscore. Input is the league names from where I grabbed the schedule.



**SKIP THIS STEP IF NOT A NEW LEAGUE, IF JUST ADDING UPCOMING SCHEDULE FOR EXISTING LEAGUE**
6. Add [league name tab in Google Sheets upcoming schedule doc] to const LEAGUE_CONFIGS in import-from-sheets.cjs

*Make sure to specify if league is in Upcoming Schedule Document #2




7. Run node import-from-sheets.cjs in Copy of THPORTHINDEX




8. Add to const LEAGUE_TO_COLLECTION_MAP in index.js of channel-lookup-deploy the mapping for [FlashLive API league name] : [league name tab in Google Sheets upcoming schedule doc]




9. Deploy index.js in channel-lookup-deploy folder in Terminal:

gcloud functions deploy channel-lookup \
  --gen2 \
  --region=us-central1 \
  --runtime=nodejs20 \
  --entry-point=channelLookupHandler \
  --trigger-http \
  --allow-unauthenticated



10. Manually trigger index.js in same folder:

curl -X POST https://us-central1-flashlive-daily-scraper.cloudfunctions.net/channel-lookup


Note:

To add league-wide channel data:
Add League and Channel to LeagueChannels tab in Google Sheets upcoming schedule document (last tab), then run node import-from-sheets.js, then manually trgigger index.js in channel-lookup-deploy folder

